This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image editing and segmentation. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed architecture and training scheme could also be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of synthetic training data suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
